{"tid":2319519,"cid":4,"subCid":0,"title":"Facebook有機會要出售Whatsapp Instagram","createTime":"2020-12-10T07:03:30.000Z","updateTime":"2020-12-12T14:18:34.000Z","uid":158977,"like":16,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":8,"replies":[{"pid":"8f62b8ccf5d139b50952daae8b0850f46b87fbf5","tid":2319519,"uid":158977,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-10T07:03:30.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/press-releases/2020/12/ftc-sues-facebook-illegal-monopolization\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fpress-releases%2F2020%2F12%2Fftc-sues-facebook-illegal-monopolization&d=DJHqE1tJ5F0S1%2BmpD1KYplMsCyrUT%2FuZDySwcdaP%2B5k%3D&h=e184054e\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/press-releases/2020/12/ftc-sues-facebook-illegal-monopolization</a><br />\n<br />\noncc唔知企邊邊<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />唔貼link<br />\n<br />\n美國聯邦貿易委員會（FTC）、48個州份周三（9日）向Facebook（Fb）提出兩項反壟斷訴訟，指後者早年收購社交平台Instagram（Ig）及通訊軟件WhatsApp屬反競爭行為。Fb成為繼科技公司Google後，第二間遭美國政府就競爭問題提出訴訟的大型科企。<br />\n申訴指，Fb在2012年以10億美元（約78億港元）及於2014年以190億美元（約148.2億港元），分別收購Ig及Whatsapp，做法濫用市場主導地位，屬於反競爭行為。FTC尋求法院頒布永久禁令，<span class=\"red\">強迫Fb出售Ig和WhatsApp</span>；各州政府則要求，日後Fb推動1,000萬美元（約7,800萬港元）或以上的收購計劃，要通報州政府官員。<br />\nFb法律顧問紐斯特德（Jennifer Newstead）認為，Fb向發展中的軟件投資數十億，令它們受惠，而反壟斷法並不存在要懲罰「成功企業」。她又質疑針對Fb引起損害的指控，稱Whatsapp成為免費軟件，讓消費者有所得益。政府是想推倒重來，令商界感到寒意。<br />\n美國政府非首次因商業競爭引起的壟斷行為而提告，司法部早在10月時控告Google母公司Alphabet，以同樣手法主導市場。<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">tldr如果facebook輸咗要賣返Whatsapp Instagram出嚟</span>"},{"pid":"74625a4b4fe0296469b9cf112a905256fb1d6dce","tid":2319519,"uid":68598,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-10T07:04:45.000Z","msg":"令商界感到寒意<br />\n建議將總部搬去支那感受下<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/eating.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e5d2478fa27c2ef8f9eceac1d8f41c5eaa8ac303","tid":2319519,"uid":22553,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-10T07:22:46.00